  <span id="freeText509555363438364540" style="display:none">Columbine by Dave Cullen is such a heartbreaking book, but it will also make you extremely angery too.<br />I can't believe this was 21 years ago I can still remember watching this on the news and sitting with friends thinking how the hell can two young boys our age do something like this.<br />Answer: one narcissistic psychopath and one extremely manic depressive who just wanted a way out (I'm sorry to say this but I'm pretty sure he could of just delt with it himself without harming others) <br />This book opens your eyes to how and what people think and how well everything is kept hidden, It also takes you on the horrendous journey from the planning to the actual disaster, the People and communities recovery oh and the police cover up.<br />There are so many people at fault in this book because they see what they want to but also these two boys are 100% at fault but I still had a little voice inside saying if only......</span>
